     891                 :            : // Test different ways settings can be merged, and verify results. This test can
     892                 :            : // be used to confirm that updates to settings code don't change behavior
     893                 :            : // unintentionally.
     894                 :            : //
     895                 :            : // The test covers:
     896                 :            : //
     897                 :            : // - Combining different setting actions. Possible actions are: configuring a
     898                 :            : //   setting, negating a setting (adding "-no" prefix), and configuring/negating
     899                 :            : //   settings in a network section (adding "main." or "test." prefixes).
     900                 :            : //
     901                 :            : // - Combining settings from command line arguments and a config file.
     902                 :            : //
     903                 :            : // - Combining SoftSet and ForceSet calls.
     904                 :            : //
     905                 :            : // - Testing "main" and "test" network values to make sure settings from network
     906                 :            : //   sections are applied and to check for mainnet-specific behaviors like
